# ShoppingListAPI

ShoppingListAPI is a simple API allowing users to create, read, update and delete
shoppinglists

## Register [/auth/register]


### Register a new user [POST]

You may register a new user using this action. It takes a JSON
object containing a name, email and password

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "user": "dkam11",
            "Email": "dkam11@gmail.com",
            "Password": "secret",
            "Firstname": "deo",
            "Surname": "kamara",
            
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /auth/register

    + Body

            {
                "Status": "Johndoe@gmail.com Successfully registered",
                "id": "eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJleHAiOjE1MDIwNzA2MTEsImlhdCI6MTUwMjA2NzAxMSwic3ViIjo0fQ.QwmwUemah0Hl7C5EXBPS36qFlNV5-iN8pJx78jimdrI"
            }
            
## Login [/auth/login]            

### Login a user [POST]

You may login a user using this action. It takes a JSON
object containing an email and password

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "user": "dkam11",
            "Password": "secret"
            
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /auth/login

    + Body

            {
                "Welcome": "dkam11",
                "token": "eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJpZCI6MSwiZXhwIjoxNTEzNzgzMzQzfQ.A4Bfos-f6-Nm9fLmd6etANFR-i1wdbtaX6UQIhtiBaM"
            }
            
            
## Logout [/auth/logout/]            

### Logout a user [POST]

You may logout a user using this action. 

+ Request (application/json)
     + Headers
     
            x-access-token: Token
        

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /logout/

## Rest password [/auth/RestPassword/]            

### Logout a user [POST]

You may rest a user's password using this action. 

+ Request (application/json)
     + Headers
     
            x-access-token: Token
    + Body
    
            {
                "Newpassword": "Secret1",
                "Username": "dkam11",
                "pass":"secret"
                    
            }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /RestPassword/
